{
  "stem": "21527.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just left the whole flat with the furniture, with everything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't know what it-- because I've never been back to Warsaw, so I don't know what happened to it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, we lived with the extended family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had an aunt and an uncle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Luba and Eugene Treyvish, and their daughter, Hanecka Treyvish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my paternal grandmother lived with us also.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was a-- the flat that we lived in had about five rooms.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my uncle was a doctor, so in the biggest room in the flat was the surgery.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then there was a waiting room.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the other three rooms we lived in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So there were three-- there were seven of us living in this place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Once the Russians came, my father got a job as an accountant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went to a Russian kindergarten.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My uncle worked as a-- he was a-- he was a surgeon, general surgeon and an orthopedic surgeon.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So he worked in the main hospital in Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And life just went on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We didn't suffer terribly much.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Russians thought, I think, that they were going to occupy Bialystok for a long, long time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were quite settled there, till June 1941, when the Germans broke the pact and invaded Russia, which meant that Bialystok was also invaded.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was actually a Russian kindergarten, so I-- there was-- I learned a little bit of reading and writing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I learned Russian, because everything was conducted in Russian.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was my first introduction to another language.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And because my grandmother lived with us and she spoke mainly Yiddish, it was at that time that I started to pick up bits and pieces of Yiddish as well.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
